C%20a%20direct%20confrontation%20with%20NATO%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ingram.%20%26quot%3BBut%20he%20thinks%20in%20a%20different%20way%20and%20plans%20in%20a%20different%20way%20to%20we%20do%20in%20the%20West%2C%20and%20therefore%20the%20way%20NATO%20countries%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20his%20ambition%20in%20growing%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20that%20he%20will%20attack%20NATO%20and%20NATO%20countries%20next%20year.%20But%20he%20will%20set%20the%20conditions%20to%20be%20able%20to%2C%20%26quot%3B%20Ingram%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20like%20Ingram%20believe%20that%20Putin%20realizes%20attacking%20NATO%20now%20would%20exact%20a%20vast%20and%20punishing%20cost%20on%20Russia.%20Instead%2C%20Putin%20will%20seek%20to%20weaken%20NATO%20from%20within%20to%20create%20soft%20spots%20he%20can%20strike%20in%20the%20future%20if%20he%20chooses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20do%20this%2C%20Putin%20will%20likely%20intensify%20Russia's%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bhybrid%20warfare%26quot%3B%20against%20NATO%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nato.int%2Fdocu%2Freview%2Farticles%2F2024%2F04%2F26%2Frussias-hybrid-war-against-the-west%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENATO%3C%2Fa%3E%20puts%20it%2C%20hybrid%20warfare%20%26quot%3Boften%20plays%20out%20in%20gray%20zones%20below%20the%20threshold%20of%20a%20conventional%20war.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20instruments%20or%20tools%20employed%20and%20fused%20together%20to%20unleash%20hybrid%20warfare%20are%20often%20difficult%20to%20discern%2C%20attribute%2C%20and%20corroborate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20can%20include%20spreading%20conspiracy%20theories%20and%20disinformation%2C%20boosting%20extremist%20parties%20in%20certain%20countries%2C%20stoking%20terror%20threats%2C%20and%20launching%20cyber%20attacks%20to%20undermine%20the%20foundation%20of%20Western%20societies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20threat%20posed%20by%20Russia%20to%20NATO%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20an%20invasion%2C%20it's%20more%20likely%20to%20come%20from%20a%20range%20of%20other%20military%20and%20non-military%20threats%20-%20what%20are%20often%20called%20hybrid%20threats%2C%26quot%3B%20Ruth%20Deyermond%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20the%20Russian%20military%20at%20King's%20College%20London%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20core%20aim%20is%20to%20prise%20away%20the%20US%20from%20its%20commitment%20to%20defend%20its%20European%20allies%2C%20either%20by%20hoping%20it%20gets%20embroiled%20in%20another%20costly%20military%20campaign%20elsewhere%2C%20or%20tires%20of%20the%20NATO%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20this%20reason%2C%20I%20expect%20we'll%20see%20Russia%20using%20all%20of%20the%20tricks%20and%20capabilities%20in%20its%20cupboard%20to%20undermine%20Western%20unity%20over%20the%20years%20to%20come%2C%26quot%3B%20Bryden%20Spurling%2C%20an%20analyst%20with%20the%20RAND%20Corporation%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20covert%20war%20is%20already%20underway%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20some%20point%20out%2C%20is%20already%20engaged%20in%20a%20war%20with%20NATO%2C%20albeit%20covertly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20days%20ago%2C%20a%20group%20of%20men%20in%20the%20UK%20were%20accused%20of%20conducting%20arson%20attacks%20on%20a%20Ukraine-linked%20business%20on%20behalf%20of%20Russian%20intelligence.%20This%20is%20just%20one%20example%20of%20%26quot%3Bhybrid%20warfare%26quot%3B%20tactics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20months%2C%20Russia%20has%20also%20been%20accused%20of%20being%20behind%20the%20scrambling%20of%20GPS%20plane%20navigation%20systems%20in%20northern%20Europe%20and%20the%20Baltics%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-electronic-warfare-messing-gps-nearby-countries-isw-ukraine-poland-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20what%20some%20claim%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20part%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bhybrid%20warfare%26quot%3B%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20Dover%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20international%20security%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hull%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20said%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20Russia%20will%20attack%20NATO%20is%20already%20redundant.%20%26quot%3BRussia%20is%20already%20engaged%20in%20a%20meaningful%20conflict%20with%20NATO%20countries%20and%20their%20allies%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ukraine%20war%20exposed%20serious%20limits%20to%20NATO's%20military%20power.%20The%20alliance%20has%20struggled%20to%20produce%20enough%20artillery%20shells%20and%20ammunition%20for%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20recent%20block%20in%20US%20aid%2C%20European%20NATO%20countries%20were%20unable%20to%20make%20up%20the%20shortfall%2C%20and%20Ukraine's%20forces%20were%20being%20outfired%20at%20a%20rate%20of%2010-one%20on%20parts%20of%20the%20front%20line%2C%20which%20were%20close%20to%20collapse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20recently%20released%20the%20aid%2C%20but%20the%20problems%20the%20situation%20exposed%20run%20deep%2C%20said%20Spurling%2C%20the%20RAND%20analyst.%20This%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20a%20weakness%20Russia%20could%20seek%20to%20exploit%20if%20not%20remedied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20conflict%20has%20exposed%20how%20underprepared%20Western%20militaries%20are%20for%20war%20that's%20not%20on%20their%20terms%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20we%20maintain%20that%20fragility%2C%20there%20is%20a%20greater%20risk%20that%20Russia%20thinks%20it%20could%20chance%20its%20arm%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERussia%20is%20weakened%20by%20the%20Ukraine%20war%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20military%20Ukraine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659d3e3c6979d73718218e44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22654%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20member%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20Territorial%20Defence%20Forces%20walks%20past%20destroyed%20Russian%20military%20vehicles%20in%20a%20forest%20outside%20Ukraine's%20second-biggest%20city%20of%20Kharkiv%20on%20March%207%2C%202022.%3Cp%3ESERGEY%20BOBOK%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Russia%20also%20faces%20massive%20problems%20of%20its%20own.%20Its%20military%20has%20been%20devasted%20by%20the%20Ukraine%20invasion.%20According%20to%20US%20estimates%2C%20its%20entire%20pre-war%20invasion%20force%20of%20around%20300%2C000%20men%20has%20been%20killed%20or%20injured%20(though%20it%20has%20replenished%20those%20numbers)%2C%20its%20stock%20of%20armored%20vehicles%20has%20been%20devastated%2C%20and%20its%20commanders%20have%20made%20consistently%20bad%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20imagine%20a%20near-%20or%20medium-term%20scenario%20in%20which%20the%20Russian%20government%20has%20the%20resources%20to%20engage%20in%20another%20war%20on%20anything%20like%20the%20scale%20of%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20Deyermond%2C%20the%20expert%20on%20the%20Russian%20military%20at%20King's%20College%20London%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20potential%20attack%20on%20NATO%20would%20come%20at%20such%20a%20devastating%20cost%20it%20could%20imperil%20Putin's%20grip%20on%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWar%20with%20NATO%20would%20destroy%20Russia%2C%20as%20Putin%20will%20know%20very%20well%2C%20and%20even%20if%20he%20thinks%20there's%20a%20possibility%20that%20the%20US%20might%20not%20step%20up%20to%20defend%20a%20fellow%20NATO%20member%20from%20a%20Russian%20invasion%2C%20he%20shows%20no%20sign%20of%20wanting%20to%20find%20out%20by%20playing%20nuclear%20Russian%20roulette%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Deyermond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20however%20long%20it%20takes%2C%20Putin%20is%20determined%20to%20achieve%20some%20form%20of%20victory%20in%20Ukraine%20so%20that%20he%20can%20use%20it%20as%20a%20platform%20to%20plan%20Russia's%20next%20campaign%2C%20said%20Ingram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Ukraine%2C%20Putin%20will%20survey%20the%20field%20and%20be%20keen%20to%20exploit%20further%20opportun