0him%2C%20that%20means%20it's%20served%20anywhere%20from%20warm%20to%20room%20temperature%20as%20long%20as%20it's%20in%20compliance%20with%20the%20Department%20of%20Health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20temperature%20allows%20the%20rice%20to%20stick%20together%20when%20you%20shape%20and%20serve%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20the%20cool%20temperature%20of%20the%20fish%20and%20warm%20sushi%20rice%20achieves%20the%20umami%20experience.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20chef%2C%20understanding%20that%20importance%20is%20paramount%2C%20Morimoto%20said.%20So%20if%20the%20rice%20is%20cold%20and%20hard%2C%20that%20could%20be%20a%20bad%20sign%20of%20everything%20else%20that's%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20fish%20shouldn't%20be%20even%20close%20to%20frozen%20when%20it's%20served%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sushi%20on%20bamboo%20trays%20on%20plate%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662fb9860dfb1341e9003f3f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20fish%20in%20your%20sushi%20should%20never%20seem%20frozen.%20%3Cp%3EMoment%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20art%20of%20serving%20exotic%20and%2For%20seasonal%20higher-end%20sushi%2C%20the%20use%20of%20frozen%20fish%20is%20a%20must%20in%20so%20many%20ways%20nowadays%2C%26quot%3B%20Morimoto%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20prep%20of%20service%20and%20proper%20thawing%20and%20shelf%20life%20management%20is%20more%20of%20the%20key.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20described%20the%20texture%20of%20frozen%20or%20near-frozen%20fish%20as%20trying%20to%20bite%20through%20a%20semi-frozen%20stick%20of%20butter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20frozen%20ingredients%20are%20necessary%2C%20thawing%20them%20properly%20is%20crucial.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWasabi%20should%20be%20freshly%20grated%2C%20not%20packaged%3C%2Fstr