r%20disclosure%20with%20our%20list%20of%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details).%20However%2C%20our%20opinions%20are%20our%20own.%20See%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-finance-editorial-standards%23rating-credit-cards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20credit%20cards%20to%20write%20unbiased%20product%20reviews%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jen%20glantz%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663007910dfb1341e90084e1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Jen%20Glantz.%3Cp%3EGaby%20Deimeke%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhen%20I%20was%20a%20kid%2C%20my%20mom%20told%20me%20credit%20cards%20could%20only%20spend%20money%20we%20already%20had.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOnce%20I%20realized%20that%20was%20a%20lie%2C%20though%2C%20I%20decided%20it%20was%20a%20good%20strategy%20for%20my%20own%20finances.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20use%20my%20credit%20cards%20strategically%2C%20and%20I%20only%20have%20three%20of%20them%20at%20any%20given%20time.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20a%20kid%2C%20my%20mom%20lied%20to%20me%20and%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-credit-cards%5C%22%3Ecredit%20cards%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20the%20same%20as%20debit%20cards.%20She%20made%20it%20very%20clear%20that%20before%20using%20either%20card%2C%20it%20was%20important%20to%20double-check%20that%20we%20had%20the%20cash%20available%20in%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-bank-account-bonuses%5C%22%3Ebank%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20afford%20the%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20start%20of%20our%20shopping%20trips%2C%20she%20would%20tell%20me%20how%20much%20we%20could%20afford%20to%20spend.%20Then%2C%20rather%20than%20mindlessly%20piling%20items%20into%20the%20cart%20when%20we'd%20stroll%20around%20department%20stores%2C%20she'd%20ask%20me%20to%20hold%20a%20calculator%20and%20add%20up%20what%20we%20intended%20to%20buy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20the%20trip%2C%20she'd%20hand%20me%20a%20credit%20card%20and%20tell%20me%20that%20it%20was%20preloaded%20with%20the%20exact%20amount%20that%20we%20had%20budgeted%20for%20this%20trip.%20I%20spent%20a%20good%20part%20of%20my%20childhood%20thinking%20that%20was%20how%20credit%20cards%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2018%2C%20the%20lie%20wore%20off.%20I%20got%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-starter-credit-cards%5C%22%3Efirst%20credit%20card%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20understood%20that%20it%20was%20very%20different%20from%20a%20debit%20card.%20While%20I%20could%20borrow%20money%20to%20afford%20a%20couple%20thousand%20dollars%20worth%20of%20purchases%2C%20the%20longer%20it%20took%20to%20pay%20off%20those%20transactions%2C%20the%20more%20interest%20I'd%20have%20to%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20the%20mindset%20that%20my%20credit%20card%20was%20the%20same%20as%20my%20debit%20card%20helped%20me%20stay%20out%20of%20debt%20over%20the%20years.%20Here's%20how%20my%20mom%20taught%20me%20to%20have%20a%20good%20relationship%20with%20credit%20cards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20I%20don't%20treat%20credit%20cards%20as%20a%20way%20to%20borrow%20money%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20never%20viewed%20my%20credit%20card%20as%20a%20means%20to%20access%20borrowed%20money.%20Instead%2C%20I%20have%20always%20viewed%20it%20as%20a%20debit%20card%20that%20comes%20with%20added%20perks%2C%20like%20cash%20back%20or%20travel%20rewards.%20Whenever%20I%20needed%20to%20make%20a%20big%20purchase%2C%20I%20waited%20until%20I%20had%20enough%20money%20in%20my%20savings%20account%20so%20that%20I%20could%20buy%20it%20with%20my%20credit%20card%20and%20pay%20it%20off%20in%20the%20same%20billing%20cycle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20avoid%20overspending%20or%20pulling%20cash%20out%20of%20my%20emergency%20fund%20to%20cover%20a%20higher-than-usual%20credit%20card%20bill%2C%20I've%20gotten%20in%20the%20habit%20of%20checking%20up%20on%20my%20finances%20weekly.%20Every%20Sunday%2C%20I'll%20look%20over%20my%20credit%20card%20statement%20to%20track%20and%20assess%20my%20spending.%20I'll%20also%20take%20a%20pulse%20on%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20finances%2C%20from%20my%20savings%20account%20balance%20to%20upcoming%20bills%20that%20I%20know%20I'll%20be%20hit%20with%20(from%20rent%20to%20utilities%20or%20health%20bills)%20to%20update%20my%20spending%20balance%20for%20the%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeeping%20a%20close%20eye%20on%20my%20credit%20card%20spending%20has%20helped%20me%20control%20overspending%20and%20instead%20stick%20to%20a%20realistic%20budget%20based%20on%20my%20overall%20cash%20flow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20I%20use%20my%20credit%20cards%20strategically%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20there%20have%20been%20a%20few%20instances%20when%20I%20had%20to%20use%20my%20credit%20card%20to%20cover%20costs%20that%20I%20couldn't%20afford%20at%20the%20moment.%20But%20even%20before%20I%20used%20my%20credit%20card%20to%20cover%20those%20costs%2C%20I%20had%20a%20plan%20for%20how%20I%20was%20going%20to%20pay%20off%20the%20balance%20without%20incurring%20high%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20in%202016%2C%20I%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20my%20full-time%20job%20and%20had%20to%20move%20to%20a%20new%20apartment.%20The%20move%20came%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20costs%20that%20I%20didn't%20have%20the%20cash%20for%20at%20the%20moment.%20My%20credit%20card%20balance%20was%20a%20couple%20of%20thousand%20dollars%2C%20and%20my%20interest%20rate%20was%20over%2020%25.%20I%20knew%20that%20once%20I%20started%20working%20again%20I%20could%20save%20money%20from%20the%20steady%20paycheck%20to%20pay%20off%20this%20balance%20in%20just%20a%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20opened%20up%20a%20new%20credit%20card%20with%200%25%20APR%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-no-fee-credit-card%5C%22%3Eno%20annual%20fee%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20did%20a%20balance%20transfer%20and%20moved%20the%20balance%20to%20this%20new%20card.%20Because%20it%20wasn't%20incurring%20any%20additional%20interest%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20pay%20off%20the%20balance%20in%20less%20than%206%20months%20without%20having%20to%20pay%20any%20extra%20fees%20or%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20isn't%20something%20I%20do%20often%2C%20it%20has%20helped%20in%20emergency%20situations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20I%20limit%20how%20many%20credit%20cards%20I%20have%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20my%20mom%20instilled%20a%20very%20strict%20set%20of%20parameters%20around%20credit%20card%20usage%20when%20I%20was%20a%20kid%2C%20it%20made%20me%20shy%20away%20from%20opening%20up%20a%20lot%20of%20credit%20cards.%20I%20had%20a%20rule%20for%20myself%20that%20at%20any%20given%20time%2C%20I%20would%20only%20have%20three%20active%20credit%20cards%20that%20I%20use.%20One%20is%20for%20personal%20use%2C%20one%20is%20for%20my%20business%2C%20and%20one%20is%20a%20joint%20credit%20card%20that%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20use%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20credit%20cards%20makes%20it%20easy%20to%20track%20spending%20and%20allows%20me%20to%20stick%20to%20the%20mindset%20that%20credit%20cards%20are%20like%20debit%20cards.%20I%20prefer%20to%20act%20like%20my%20mom%20was%20telling%20me%20the%20truth%20about%20credit%20cards.%20It's%20helped%20me%20stay%20out%20of%20debt%2C%20keep%20a%20close%20eye%20on%20my%20spending%2C%20and%20prevent%20me%20from%20becoming%20an%20impulsive%20shopper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-mom-lied-about-credit-card-works-glad-listened-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714566901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6630078c0dfb1