n't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%2C%20made%20outside%20normal%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20Microsoft%20made%20an%20initial%20%241%20billion%20investment%20into%20its%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-openai-antitrust-watchdog-partnership-merger-probe-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emulti-billion-dollar%20partnership%20with%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20has%20since%20benefited%20from%20its%20well-timed%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20public%20and%20investor%20interest%20in%20AI%20surged%20post-%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-changed-everything-and-was-a-black-swan-event-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Microsoft%20was%20able%20to%20move%20quickly%2C%20incorporating%20OpenAI's%20buzzy%20tech%20into%20existing%20products%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-bings-ai-chatbots-new-styles-respond-to-basic-questions-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBing%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Microsoft%20365.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20speed%20at%20which%20Microsoft%20released%20AI%20products%20even%20left%20some%20wondering%20whether%20its%20arch-rival%20Google%20had%20been%20left%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%2C%20a%20pioneer%20of%20AI%20technology%2C%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20counter%20the%20narrative%20that%20it%20has%20fallen%20behind%20Microsoft%20ever%20since.%20The%20company%20released%20several%20products%20to%20compete%20with%20OpenAI's%20releases%2C%20including%20Bard%2C%20an%20AI-powered%20chatbot%2C%20and%20an%20AI%20model%20named%20Gemini.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202019%20email%20exchanges%20also%20show%20how%20Microsoft%20was%20keeping%20tabs%20on%20its%20rivals%2C%20with%20Scott%20saying%20the%20scale%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20DeepMind%2C%20and%20Google%20Brain's%20AI%20ambitions%20were%20%26quot%3Binteresting.%26quot%3B%20Among%20some%20of%20the%20mentions%20of%20what%20its%20competitors%20were%20doing%2C%20Scott%20mentioned%20Google's%20data-center%20designs%20and%20distributed-systems%20architecture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiscussing%20Microsoft's%20AI%20talent%2C%20Scott%20said%20it%20had%20%26quot%3Bvery%20smart%26quot%3B%20people%20with%20machine-learning%20expertise%20in%20its%20Bing%2C%20vision%2C%20and%20speech%20teams.%20He%20added%20that%20the%20teams%20faced%20constraints%20on%20scaling%20up%20their%20ambitions%2C%20which%20suggests%20why%20Microsoft%20saw%20potential%20in%20partnering%20with%20OpenAI%20to%20bring%20its%20AI%20aspirations%20to%20fruition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20added%20that%20when%20Open%20AI%2C%20Deep%20Mind%2C%20and%20Google%20Brain%20were%20competing%20to%20see%20who%20could%20achieve%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20impressive%20game-playing%20stunt%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20dismissive%20of%20their%20efforts%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20%26quot%3Bthat%20was%20a%20mistake.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20unredacted%20portions%20of%20the%20emails%20below.%20RL%20refers%20to%20reinforcement%20learning%2C%20NLP%20is%20natural%20language%20processing%2C%20and%20BERT%20is%20bidirectional%20encoder%20representations%20from%20transformers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Kevin%20Scott%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cstrong%3ESent%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Wednesday%2C%20June%2012%2C%202019%207%3A16%3A11%20AM%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cstrong%3ETo%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Satya%20Nadella%3B%20Bill%20Gates%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cstrong%3ESubject%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Re%3A%20Thoughts%20on%20OpenAI%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%5BRedacted%5D%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20thing%20that's%20interesting%20about%20what%20Open%20AI%20and%20Deep%20Mind%20and%20Google%20Brain%20are%20doing%20is%20the%20scale%20of%20their%20ambition%2C%20and%20how%20that%20ambition%20is%20driving%20everything%20from%20datacenter%20design%20to%20compute%20silicon%20to%20networks%20and%20distributed%20systems%20architectures%20to%20numerical%20optimizers%2C%20compiler%2C%20programming%20frameworks%2C%20and%20the%20high%20level%20abstractions%20that%20model%20developers%20have%20at%20their%20disposal.%20When%20all%20these%20programs%20were%20doing%20was%20competing%20with%20one%20another%20to%20see%20which%20RL%20system%20could%20achieve%20the%20most%20impressive%20game-playing%20stunt%2C%20I%20has%20highly%20dismissive%20of%20their%20efforts.%20That%20was%20a%20mistake.%20When%20they%20took%20all%20of%20the%20infrastructure%20that%20they%20had%20built%20to%20build%20NLP%20models%20that%20we%20couldn't%20easily%20replicate%2C%20I%20started%20to%20take%20things%20more%20seriously.%20And%20as%20I%20dug%20in%20to%20try%20to%20understand%20where%20all%20of%20the%20capability%20gaps%20were%20between%20Google%20and%20us%20for%20model%20training%2C%20I%20got%20very%2C%20very%20worried.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ETurns%20out%2C%20just%20replicating%20BERT-large%20wasn't%20easy%20to%20do%20for%20us.%20Even%20though%20we%20had%20the%20template%20for%20the%20model%2C%20it%20took%20us%20~6%20months%20to%20get%20the%20model%20trained%20because%20our%20infrastructure%20wasn't%20up%20to%20the%20task.%20Google%20had%20BERT%20for%20at%20least%20six%20months%20prior%20to%20that%2C%20so%20in%20the%20time%20that%20it%20took%20us%20to%20hack%20together%20the%20capability%20to%20train%20a%20340M%20parameter%20model%2C%20they%20had%20a%20year%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20get%20it%20into%20production%20and%20to%20move%20on%20to%20larger%20scale%2C%20more%20interesting%20models.%20We%20are%20already%20seeing%20the%20results%20of%20that%20work%20in%20our%20competitive%20analysis%20of%20their%20products.%20One%20of%20the%20Q%26amp%3BA%20competitive%20metrics%20that%20we%20watch%20just%20jumped%20by%2010%20percentage%20points%20on%20Google%20Search%20because%20of%20BERT-like%20models.%20Their%20auto-complete%20in%20Gmail%2C%20which%20is%20especially%20useful%20in%20the%20mobile%20app%2C%20is%20getting%20scarily%20good.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%5BRedacted%5D%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EWe%20have%20very%20smart%20ML%20people%20in%20Bind%2C%20in%20the%20vision%20team%2C%20and%20in%20the%20speech%20team.%20But%20the%20core%20deep%20learning%20teams%20within%20each%20of%20these%20bigger%20teams%20are%20very%20small%2C%20and%20their%20ambitions%20have%20also%20been%20constrained%2C%20which%20means%20that%20even%20as%20we%20start%20to%20feed%20them%20resources%2C%20they%20still%20have%20to%20go%20through%20a%20learning%20process%20to%20scale%20up.%20And%20we%20are%20multiple%20years%20behind%20the%20competition%20in%20terms%20of%20ML%20scale.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%5BRedacted%5D%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Satya%20Nadella%3Cbr%3E%3Cstrong%3ETo%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Kevin%20Scott%3Cbr%3E%3Cstrong%3ECC%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Amy%20Hood%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cstrong%3ESent%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%206%2F12%2F2019%206%3A02%3A47%20PM%3Cbr%3E%3Cstrong%3ESubject%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Re%3A%20Thoughts%20on%20OpenAI%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EVery%20good%20email%20that%20explains%2C%20why%20I%20want%20us%20to%20do%20this%E2%80%A6%20and%20also%20why%20we%20will%20then%20ensure%20our%20infra%20folks%20execute.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EAmy%20-%20fyi%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ESent%20from%20Mail%20for%20Windows%2010%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsatya-nadella-bill-gates-microsoft-concern-google-rivals-ai-emails-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714561715000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663208ce10dfcda409652d5a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsatya-nadella-bill-gates-microsoft-concern-google-rivals-ai-emails-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Microsoft's%20concern%20about%20Google'